@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@next "Distribution"
@prev "Main"
@{b}Introduction@{ub}

DumpCatalogue is a small filedumper for the filecatalogue.  I have
been programming on it now and then.  I thought I'd release it for
others to enjoy it.  It's primary use is to make fast filelistings
without any fuzz.  Maybe you want to save the descriptions for
later use when you harddrive breaks down?

@endnode

@node "Distribution" "Distribution"
@next "Responsibility"
@prev "Introduction"
@{b}Distribution@{ub}

This version of DumpCatalogue is freely distributable for
non-commercial use.

You can spread this complete archive via AmiNet, ADS, SAN and
other non-profit networks and BBS:es.

@endnode

